This paper deals with coding schemes for storing information in flash memory, which involves a combination of information theory, data structures, distributed computing, and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
